      • compareTo

        public int compareTo(Spring other)
        Compares this Spring to a given other Spring. This one is greater than the other one, when the higher index of its two masses is is higher than the others higher index of that masses. If they are equal, the same comparison is performed on the masses of each spring, that has the lower index. If both Springs are equal, zero is returned.

        This is used in GraphConverter to sort the springs for the connection map output.

        Specified by:
        compareTo in interface Comparable<Spring>
        Parameters:
        other - The Spring to compare this to.
        Returns:
        An int lower to zero, if this is lower than other, zero, if this is equals other, or greater zero, if this is greater other.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - If the argument is null.
